{"name": "mkdocs-drawio-converter", "metadata": {"name": "mkdocs-drawio-converter", "version": "1.0.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Documentation", "Topic :: Software Development :: Documentation"], "home_page": "https://github.com/rajneesh-ril/mkdocs-drawio-converter", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["mkdocs"], "summary": "MkDocs plugin to convert Drawio files to SVG format", "upload_time": 1734424937}, "documentation": ["# README.md\n# MkDocs Drawio Converter Plugin\n\nA MkDocs plugin that automatically converts Drawio (.drawio) files to SVG format during the build process.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install mkdocs-drawio-converter\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Draw.io desktop app installed (for the CLI tool)\n- MkDocs\n\n## Configuration\n\nAdd the following to your `mkdocs.yml`:\n\n```yaml\nplugins:\n  - drawio-converter:\n      drawio_executable: /path/to/drawio  # Path to drawio executable\n      source_dir: docs                    # Directory containing .drawio files\n      output_dir: svg                     # Directory for output SVG files\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n1. Place your .drawio files in your docs directory\n2. Build your MkDocs site\n3. Reference the converted SVG files in your markdown:\n\n```markdown\n![My Diagram](svg/diagram.svg)\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mkdocs_drawio_converter", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "mkdocs_drawio_converter.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkdocs_drawio_converter.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "mkdocs_drawio_converter.PackageNotFoundError", "xref": {"fqname": "importlib.metadata.PackageNotFoun